OL,3,CPlans put forward to suspend
OL,4,Cpolitician for third time in six months
OL,6,FThose responsible for overseeing
OL,7,Fpoliticians' behaviour, the Privileges
OL,8,Fand Procedures Committee, brought
OL,9,Fforward the proposition - claiming
OL,10,FOzouf breached rules six and seven of
OL,11,Fthe Code of Conduct.
OL,13,FRule six states that "members must not
OL,14,Fact or behave in a manner in the
OL,15,Fcourse of their public and private
OL,16,Flife" that brings the Assembly or its
OL,17,FMembers "generally into disrepute and
OL,18,Fshould conduct themselves in a manner
OL,19,Fwhich strengthens the public's trust
OL,20,Fand confidence" in Jersey States.
