OL,3,CPlans put forward to suspend
OL,4,Cpolitician for third time in six months
OL,6,FMeanwhile, rule seven explains that
OL,7,Fpoliticians "must uphold the law in
OL,8,Faccordance with their oath of office".
OL,10,FOzouf was first suspended from the
OL,11,FStates without pay last September
OL,12,Fafter being convicted of motoring
OL,13,Foffences and failing to attend parish
OL,14,Fhall inquiries about his offences.
OL,16,FHe was then suspended for a second
OL,17,Ftime in November - this time with pay
OL,18,F- after pleading guilty to breaking
OL,19,Fimmigration law.
