OL,3,CPlans put forward to suspend
OL,4,Cpolitician for third time in six months
OL,6,FFollowing his sentencing for that
OL,7,Fcrime, and if the majority of Jersey
OL,8,Fpoliticians agree, Ozouf would be
OL,9,Fsuspended for 28 days without pay.
OL,11,FA vote is currently scheduled for
OL,12,FTuesday 10 March but could be called
OL,13,Fearlier, potentially as soon as next
OL,14,Fweek.
OL,16,FDeputy Sam Mezec, leader of Reform
OL,17,FJersey, has supported the motion to
OL,18,Fsuspend Ozouf, writing on social
OL,19,Fmedia: "Ozouf could and should put us
OL,20,Fall out of our misery and resign from
OL,21,Fthe States."
